    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers specifically to craftsmen who create decorative sculpted surfaces and sculptural detail for walls and ceilings in stucco, which is a light, malleable plaster. Also refers generally to those who apply stucco to surfaces, not necessarily sculpted or molded.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046622/Beard, Stucco and Decorative Plasterwork (1983)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere especialmente a los artesanos que crean superficies decorativas esculpidas y detalles esculturales para paredes y techos en material estuco. Generalmente sólo se refiere a aquellos que estucan superficies, no necesariamente esculpidores o moldeadores.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst in specifieke zin naar ambachtslieden die decoratieve gebeeldhouwde oppervlakken en gebeeldhouwde details voor muren en plafonds in pleisterwerk vervaardigen en aanbrengen. Verwijst ook in het algemeen naar personen die stucwerk aanbrengen op oppervlakken, niet noodzakelijk met bepaalde (gebeeldhouwde) vormen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052403/Van Dale Groot Woordenboek (1998)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>特指以灰泥為材料，在牆面或天花板上製作裝飾性平面和細部雕刻的工匠。亦泛指以雕刻、模塑或其他方式在物體平面上塗敷灰泥者。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Artisti e artigiani specializzati in rilievi ornamentali ottenuti con lo stucco, a decorazione di oggetti d'arte, edifici, ecc.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
